'''Nikoli Shakara Manzoni''' (née '''Bowe''') (born November 17, 1965) is a Bahamian renowned singer-songwriter known for her extraordinary vocal capabilities. Born in Nassau, Bahamas, Manzoni is known for wide vocal range, performances, and distinctive style. 

== Early Life ==
{{Infobox character|name=Nikoli Shakara Manzoni|relatives=Anita Miller (mother) Anthony Bowe (father) Fabio Manzoni (husband) Natela Cortes (daughter) Marika Manzoni (daughter) Taja Manzoni-Martinez (daughter) Kaielle Manzoni (daughter) Leila Manzoni-Galore (daughter)|marital=Fabio Manzoni (1998-Present)|birthDate=April 10, 1965|birthPlace=Nassau, Bahamas|gender=Female}}
Bowe was born on November 17, 1965 in Nassau, Bahamas to Anita Miller (1921-2004) and Anthony Bowe (1920-1988). Her mother was Bahamian and her father was of Indo-Trinidadian descent. Bowe also inherited over $1,000,000 from her maternal grandfather. 
